  "texts": [
    "The min-to-max operational range values on the PLC assists with taking action and (possibly) alerting an operator, when the safety threshold is breached (see Section 6.6).",
    "Additionally, the PLCs may also include logic to act, even before a breach, by providing a warning buffer.",
    "This may be achieved by setting tighter boundary conditions.",
    "Traditionally, at least two layers of safety are provided, the lower boundary is the warning boundary which alerts operators to take action, the upper boundary is the min-max boundary, and this should never be passed.",
    "In some systems if the min-max boundary is passed the personnel must evacuate the site and services are put on hold until safe conditions are assured."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}